cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.PL, cs.AI 

The paper deals with strategy improvement algorithms for solving parity games, which are a type of two-player game. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses the implementation of these algorithms, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of one-player strategy improvement, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses parallel algorithms and GPU implementations, which fall under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages).
